<br>
10% increase first<br>
100hp * 110% = 110hp  110hp * 90% = 99hp<br>
<br>
10% reduction first<br>
100hpp * 90% = 90hp  90hp * 110% = 99hp <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaaeamdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaeamdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/30/02 3:39:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2680.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing Adept</span><hr size=1> I know that a*b*c = a*c*b.  :)  Sorry if my original question was not clear.<br>
<br>
Healing Adept 3 increases the amount healed by 10%.  There are two ways of combining this with the druid 10% healing penalty.  The first is applying either the reduction or increase first, then apply the other.  This generates Heal *1.1 *.9 for a 99% heal for druids/shamen and Heal*1.1*1.05 for a 116% heal.   The other way is to add all bonuses and penalties so for Druids/Shamen Heal * (1-0.1+0.1) = 100% and for Clerics Heal * (1+0.05+0.1) = 115%  It is just a 1% difference either way, but if anyone has HA3 it is easy to know, so I figured I would ask. <p>____________<BR>
